OL,6,FHe declined to say anything in answer
OL,7,Fto the charge. He further declined to
OL,8,Fcall any evidence or tender any
OL,9,Fwitnesses on his behalf.
OL,11,FA prosecution lawyer told the hearing
OL,12,Fthat based on the papers before him he
OL,13,Fbelieved the defendant had a prima
OL,14,Ffacie case to answer.
OL,16,FDefence barrister Stephen Molloy told
OL,17,Fthe court the defendant was appearing
OL,18,Fvia video link from his home as he is
OL,19,Fcurrently recovering from an operation
OL,20,Fon his stomach performed within the
OL,21,Fpast two weeks.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/7
